uld check if the test class uses the StyleNodeFactory call site. There might be potential import order issues to consider here as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing extension issues**\\n\\nI'm checking the streaming and schema aspects and considering whether an unknown extension instruction may cause issues when running without a license. I've spotted a potential issue with `extension-element-prefixes` on the `xsl:stylesheet`, which is in no namespace. I must evaluate how the `StyleNodeFactory` interacts here. There’s something with the `ext:emit` encountering undefined behavior when it's not a top-level element. I think I need to consider how to handle these attributes and the transformation of the output since the fallback might not output any whitespace.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added dedicated coverage test:\n\n- `tests/src/net.sf.saxon/Saxon-HE/9.9.1-6/src/test/java/net_sf_saxon/Saxon_HE/StyleNodeFactoryTest.java`\n\nThe test compiles and runs an XSLT stylesheet containing an unknown extension instruction with `xsl:fallback`. This exercises `StyleNodeFactory.makeElementNode(...)` through Saxon’s public JAXP API and should reach the remaining `Class#newInstance()` call site that creates the internal absent-extension element.\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04cdb68808904b6d0169f4d9552698819eac408d63038cfd3b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 345, "output": 641, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39386, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777654088328, "responseId": "resp_04cdb68808904b6d0169f4d948c930819eac3e62d3dce27189"}, "toolResults": []}
